               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390916-name-1452" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-1452" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-1452" type="surname" value="PUGH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-1452" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES PUGH</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in partnership with William Pugh; we are upholsterers, and live in Blackman-street, in the Borough. The prisoner was our porter for about ten weeks, and he also worked on the premises, as a mattress-maker—this property is ours.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390916-name-1453" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-1453" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-1453" type="surname" value="MYERS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-1453" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>ROBERT MYERS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a plumber, and live in Kent-street. I know</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183909160183"></xptr>
               <p>this lead—it is part of some old lead that was on the roof of Mr. Pugh's premises, and which I had cut up.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. HORRY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> If you had seen it any where else would you undertake to swear it was Mr. Pugh's? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I should—here is every mark where it was cut from the skylight—I have compared it with what is left on the roof—it corresponds with the frame of the old skylight.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390916-name-1454" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-1454" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-1454" type="surname" value="TAYLOR"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-1454" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM TAYLOR</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-sergeant M</hi> 14.) On the 16th of September, about a quarter before nine o'clock, I was passing a marine-store shop in Kent-street—I saw the prisoner in the shop, and a female there was weighing these pieces of lead—I then saw the prisoner take this brass-rail from his pocket and put it into the scale—I went in, and asked where he got it—he said it was his own property, he had bought it, and he was in the habit of attending sales, and was a jobbing master for him<lb></lb>self—I said he must go to the station-house—in going along we met a female, who said to him, "Halloo, George, where are you going?"—he made her some answer which I did not hear—these are the articles.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PUGH</hi>. These are our property.</p>
